locality: South slope of Mt. Kouakoué, along old mining road ca. 1.5 km from Ni River crossing. Partially degraded maquis and forest along roadside.
Forested slopes beneath radio tower at Mandjélia, near NE end of island.
Ridge below and west of Napupwa. Mixture of Melaleuca scrub and forest, and rainforest. Trees collected from rainforest on steep slopes.
Bois du Sud. End of side road SE from Noumea-Yate Road, near stream and picnic area.
Mt. Aoupinié: above Poya. Forested slopes, dominated by Agathis, Piliocalyx.
